  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (a44159a 2023-01-03T00:04:41.810446Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge fmt\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\n`forge fmt` does not respect the `bracket_spacing` rule for named function args:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction a(uint256 foo) public pure {\r\n    foo;\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction b() public pure {\r\n    a( {foo: 5} );\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe above gets formatted to:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\na({foo: 5});\r\n```\r\n\r\nEven if `bracket_spacing` is set to `true` in the Foundry config.\r\n\r\n#### Update\r\n\r\nIt looks like this doesn't work for structs either. This:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\namounts: Amounts({ deposit: args.amounts.netDeposit, withdrawn: 0 }),\r\n```\r\n\r\nGets re-formatted to:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\namounts: Amounts({deposit: args.amounts.netDeposit, withdrawn: 0}),\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have updated the title of the issue to mention both named args and structs.\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\nThis is my `[fmt]` configuration:\r\n\r\n```toml\r\n[fmt]\r\nbracket_spacing = true\r\nint_types = \"long\"\r\nline_length = 120\r\nmultiline_func_header = \"all\"\r\nnumber_underscore = \"thousands\"\r\nquote_style = \"double\"\r\ntab_width = 4\r\nvariable_override_spacing = false\r\nwrap_comments = true\r\n```",
